#. Tag: emphasis
msgid "Code conventions:"
msgstr ""

#: conventions.xml:100
#, no-c-format
#. Tag: para
msgid "Code and mark-up samples will be formatted in a grey block."
msgstr ""

#: conventions.xml:103
#, no-c-format
#. Tag: para
msgid "Sometimes, lines of code or mark-up examples will be longer than the page width. To avoid having them run off the page, the slash character &quot;\\&quot; is used to denote a soft line break. This means that the line of code is in reality meant to be on one line, but for print formatting, it has been broken across two or more lines."
msgstr ""

